                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C114/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-29T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1920—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>404. Your 88, May 26, 1 p.m.</p>
                <p>Mr. Root comes to The Hague primarily as a member of the Permanent Court of The
                    Hague to pass upon the Portuguese arbitration regarding church property. As you
                    know, he is also a member of the League of Nations Organizing Committee for the
                    Permanent Court of International Justice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
